My only gripe about this place is that you can't buy equipment here!  Went to get fitted for golf equipment.  Decided that after all these years I needed to finally learn and take lessons.  To do that I wanted to start off with the right equipment.  A colleague was kind enough to bring me to the personalized golf fitting.  You sign in and a professional analyzes your swing (I didn't really have one!) and decides how to customize your golf club.  It takes about 30 minutes and at the end of it you get a copy (also emailed to you), of recommended clubs and grips.  They were super nice and very friendly.  The facility itself is nothing to marvel at, it is utiliatarian and right off of the I-17, but the stuff inside is nothing short of magic.

